Brewing

Step 1.

Open Brewer (Cauldron?/or something) there are 3 item slots. 3 Fluid slots and 1 Catalyst slot. and the Final fluid slot for output.

To Brew you first need (water for tier 1, Spiritual Spring for tier 2 etc...) in first fluid input. second and third can be any potion effect
if you want too to add effects. if not theres no need in other 2 fluid inputs.

Then for the 3 Input for ingredient this is what will handle the actual recipe like maybe you put in Rice + Potato + Carrot and it will make some cool liquor.
Catalyst slot needs Spiritual Stones. Depending on the Tier of the first fluid input you need to match it with that tier of Catalyst too. as the catalyst is what
gives the Liquor its spiritual nature.

Then it will start crafting but note this will take quite a while since it is Brewing Liquor. When you got 100 Ml of liquor you need to use special (Bottle?/Gourd?)
to grab it by either right clicking the Brewing with it or inside its inventory grab the Special Item and right click it on the Output tank fluid slot.

Step 2.
Then you need to put the Liquor inside a Fermenting Barrel. Here comes the important part The longer it's in the barrel the stronger the effects of the Liquor-
so if you left it for 1 hour it would be good but if its left for 24h it would be insane (Obviously it would be limited to a specific time allowed. Configurable.)

Step 3.
When that is done you need to get the Fermented Liquor out and you can enjoy your Spiritual Liquor.